{"_type":"comment","id":1,"item_id":"019ea4fcc6877cc7ae826a5d56aec737","author":"claude","text":"Owner review feedback on the Plugin-authoring skill (couldn't be added as an annotation due to the empty-line annotation wedge bug): \"This plugin skill is woefully incomplete. It needs to include the entire plugin API and dev guide, not just caveats. Even some sample code.\" => Scope expansion: skill 3 should carry the FULL plugin API + dev guide + sample code, not only the traps/caveats. Tension to resolve: a fully-inlined API+guide+samples is very large for a self-contained skill system_prompt — this is exactly the case the seed-kbs DCR (019ea523295175) is meant to serve (ship the API/guide/samples as seeded kbs the skill references by stable key). Decide: inline-everything vs skill-points-to-seeded-kbs (needs the DCR) vs hybrid (caveats+recipe inline now, full API/guide/samples as a follow-up once kb-seeding lands).","created_at":"2026-06-08T03:04:36"}
{"_type":"comment","id":2,"item_id":"019ea4fcc6877cc7ae826a5d56aec737","author":"claude","text":"SESSION OUTCOME (2026-06-07, end of night): all 3 recut skills BUILT into codetools/manifest.json (uncommitted). Basic coding (4 tools, ephemeral scripts). Advanced coding (38 tools, durable-engineering methodology + note-vs-docket-vs-project rules + notes-as-working-memory incl. get/list_note(_tab) + capture-as-you-go/compaction). Plugin authoring (16 tools) REWRITTEN SELF-CONTAINED with the FULL plugin API inline (~11.5KB: manifest schema, stdio JSON-RPC transport+envelopes, complete host.* catalog, html/scene panels, annotation substrate recipe+signatures, lifecycle, traps, Go sample) — resolving the owner's \"woefully incomplete / needs the whole API+guide+samples\" review (the LLM on user machines lacks the source). Reviewed across several annotation+verbal rounds. Owner verdict: \"good enough.\" Remaining: reinstall to re-seed (next session), HITL in focused chats, and the inline-vs-seeded-kb decision (DCR 019ea523295) to lift the API depth into shipped kbs. Leaving this discussion active for owner to close.","created_at":"2026-06-08T03:32:18"}
{"_type":"comment","id":3,"item_id":"019eafd5683f7fb29a640a0170e97ad6","author":"agent","text":"HITL session 2 (2026-06-10): the full relay-ux-suite (6 items, tag relay-ux-suite) SHIPPED + live-verified on real Claude Code — busy-gate (no phantoms, no arm race), row anchoring (read_turn returns exactly the answer; 3 boundary bugs incl. TUI-busy-block-collapse, hint agent-relay/tui-busy-block-collapses), self-managing lifecycle (sessions resume across restart AND across remove+reinstall; armed never reaps), one-file persistence, and the new blocking tools: relay_ask one-call index loop (~10s live round-trip) + wait_turn (caught an unarmed human-style turn live). Plugins main @ 9e4da87, 129/129 tests. STILL UNTESTED LIVE (B5 remaining legs): distill model_spec, note/speak delivery, PLUGIN_EVENT trigger→chat-wake leg, codex/opencode profiles, formal non-interference proof.","created_at":"2026-06-10T22:31:01"}
{"_type":"comment","id":4,"item_id":"019eafd5683f7fb29a640a0170e97ad6","author":"claude","text":"HITL session 3 (2026-06-11): THREE more B5 legs PASSED live — (1) distill: relay_ask/read_turn with model=\"gpt-5.4-mini\" returns the pure conversational reply, distilled=true; (2) delivery: note created with timestamped title + distilled content, linked to chat, AND minerva_speak played audibly (owner-confirmed twice); (3) PLUGIN_EVENT→chat-wake: trigger relay-turn-wake (limit 3) + agent relay-listener — send→armed one-shot→settle_prompt→event→trigger fired ONCE→agent chat woke→real read_turn tool call→correct report. Zero polling. Four live bugs found+fixed+test-locked (plugins main eee4155): bogus model_spec kind 'provider'; max_tokens rejected by ChatGPT backend; router tools_list_schema drift for read_turn (drift guard test added — Minerva validates against ROUTER schema snapshotted at INSTALL, manifest unused, client /mcp snapshot stringifies unknown args: full refresh = reinstall + /mcp); create_note needs {title,content} not {text}. Core Minerva fix: minerva_speak called removed ChatPane._load_wav_into_stream → VoiceServiceClient.load_audio_into_stream (Minerva dcr/agent-relay e48390bd) — speak path worked live for the first time. REMAINING B5: codex profile calibration (codex installed, opencode NOT on this machine), formal non-interference proof, distilled=false on the internal agent-chat read_turn path (minor, uninvestigated). Polish items: per-watch default deliver options on watch_start; Minerva should enforce create_note required fields (silently creates blank note).","created_at":"2026-06-11T17:22:32"}
{"_type":"comment","id":5,"item_id":"019eafd5683f7fb29a640a0170e97ad6","author":"claude","text":"HITL session 4 (2026-06-11): CODEX PROFILE CALIBRATION leg PASSED live (plugins main 1526223). Real Codex CLI v0.139.0 fixtures captured byte-true (tests/fixtures/real/codex_{idle_prompt,busy,done,permission}.txt — extracted from MCP transcript JSONL, not retyped). Every seed parameter was wrong: prompt = › U+203A col-0 + placeholder text (seed's ^\\s*[>❯]\\s*$ matched neither char nor never-empty line → ^›\\s); busy = literal \"esc to interrupt\" in the Working line which VANISHES on completion (braille glyphs gone); permission dialogs = numbered pickers with no busy marker + ›-prefixed selector (without new dialog regex they false-fire turn_completed); alt_screen=FALSE (scrollback grew 17→23→50). 5 fixture-backed detector tests added. LIVE PROOF on real codex: relay_ask \"symbol for gold\" → distilled \"Gold's chemical symbol is Au.\", settle_prompt, one blocking call; permission leg → cause=input_requested method=permission_dialog with dialog text in payload (babysit use case viable); answered dialog → turn_completed. read_clean strips codex ─ separators (model·cwd footer line survives — minor polish). BONUS FIX: profiles/state/watcher unit tests raced on process-global PROFILES (init_profiles vs profile_set) — serialized via TEST_PROFILES_LOCK + state roundtrip restores saved bytes before load(); 8/8 stress green, 135/135 total. Hint: agent-relay/codex-profile-calibration. REMAINING for B5 done: formal non-interference proof (opencode deferred — not installed on this machine). Gotcha: codex launch needs nvm node on PATH (env-shebang).","created_at":"2026-06-11T17:54:42"}
{"_type":"comment","id":6,"item_id":"019eafd5683f7fb29a640a0170e97ad6","author":"claude","text":"HITL session 4 cont. (2026-06-11): NON-INTERFERENCE PROOF PASSED — the last planned B5 leg (comment #477 invariant). Byte leg: script(1) -I recorded codex's actual stdin over two identically-scripted runs (2 questions + /quit) in the same terminal — run A unwatched, run B under all_turns watching with read_turn/read_clean/watch_status fired mid-run. DOUBLE ASSERTION, both pass: (1) logs byte-identical after stripping script's timestamped header/trailer; (2) both equal EXACTLY the sent writes — zero surplus bytes, nothing in the watch path injects input. Human leg: owner typed/backspace-edited/approved a permission dialog via arrows/Esc-interrupted a generation in the watched terminal while reads fired — owner verdict verbatim: \"No anomalies\". Artifacts + recipe committed: tests/fixtures/proof/ (plugins main c028b99). Bonus coverage during the human pass: Esc-interrupt screen (\"Conversation interrupted\") still detected settle_prompt turn end; agent_exited fired on /quit. Exercise-list status: #1 index loop DONE (session 3), #2 non-interference DONE (this), #3 mixed-session COVERED incidentally (human+agent interleaved on one watched terminal across sessions), #4 babysit mechanics PROVEN (input_requested + dialog text in payload; full rubric-driven answer loop not separately run), #5 exit paths PARTIAL (agent_exited proven live; terminal_closed + timed_out only unit-tested). B5 arguably done — owner call on transition. Remaining beyond B5: B6 release (owner-gated push both repos, tag agent_relay-v0.1.0, registry regen w/ PLUGIN_DIRS allow-list addition); opencode profile deferred (not installed).","created_at":"2026-06-11T18:14:40"}
{"_type":"comment","id":7,"item_id":"019eafd57c6d701f9d1c68511cfc2b3d","author":"claude","text":"RELEASE PUBLISHED 2026-06-11 (owner-authorized): agent_relay-v0.1.0 live. Surprise: the FIRST main push this morning (relay-ux docket commit) had already auto-published the clean tag from 540cbb4 — STALE pre-calibration binaries under the official tag, and registry-check failing on every subsequent main push (hint minerva-plugins/plugin-ci-main-push-auto-releases). Fix: after the calibrated main push (94eb97b) built green, force-moved the tag to 94eb97b → tag-push run rebuilt all 4 targets FROM the tagged commit (provenance correct, assets refreshed 21:48Z, prerelease=false). regen_registry → registry.json advertises agent_relay (5 plugins); all 4 download URLs 302; registry-check green (run 27379615539). Pushed: plugins main 614fee1; Minerva development fast-forwarded to be35360c (dcr/agent-relay merged + pushed). REMAINING for done: fresh marketplace install on a clean profile (tools visible, skill seeded, grants applied) — owner-side HITL.","created_at":"2026-06-11T21:49:40"}
{"_type":"comment","id":8,"item_id":"019eb7f3710374f9906d6019c9f4e2b6","author":"claude","text":"SEAM CONTRACT LOCKED (MNR DCR 019eb7f329 comment #483) — supersedes parts of this item's description: (1) the <enter>/<esc> control-token convention is DELETED — input_requested returns kind:\"question\" with options:[{label, keystroke}] parsed from the dialog region; Minerva renders a question card (reused AutocoderStreamQuestionCard) and the click sends ONE keystroke back through generate dispatch. (2) Registration = CapabilityBroker ops host.chat_providers.register/unregister (declare capability in manifest), entry per watch session, generate_tool = new minerva_agent_relay_passthrough_generate (thin over relay_ask core — parallel path = review reject), history_mode newest_only, timeout_sec 600. (3) Work happens on plugins branch dcr/chat-passthrough (base 0917f9f) — NEVER main mid-initiative; manifest → 0.2.0 before final main merge.","created_at":"2026-06-11T23:23:36"}
